-> gesturing during encoding = like action in facilitating memory
-> 2 moments influencent later recall : encode/recall
-> en général effet des mvts au moment du recall
-> Speakers also gesture more when trying to remember infrequent words (which are relatively hard to recall) than when trying to remember frequent words (Beattie & Shovelton, 2000; Krauss & Hadar, 1999).
-> gesture more pas seulement parce que dur de se souvenir (qd manipule la qté de gestes, augmente nombre infos retenues)

Speakers who are told to gesture when trying to recall infrequent words in experimentally induced tip-of-the-tongue states are more likely to recall the words than speakers who are told not to gesture (Frick-Horbury & Guttentag, 1998; although see Beattie & Coughlan, 1999).

